         <abstract>
            <p>Fast closing of actuator servovalves in airplane hydraulic systems can
                            often cause unacceptably high pressure spikes in these systems. This
                            paper describes and discusses a method of reducing these hydraulic
                            system pressure spikes by suitable limiting of the rate at which the
                            servovalve current can change. Analytical and test results are presented
                            to show that with this method, the pressure spikes can be reduced
                            without significantly affecting the actuator dynamic response
                            characteristics.</p>
         </abstract>
